sentences: 69 Boyz is an American Miami bass and hip hop duo: Van "Thrill Da Playa" Bryant, from Jacksonville, Florida, and Barry "Fast" Wright, from Orlando, Florida, United States.
In 1992, Thrill da Playa and Fast Cash teamed up to form 69 Boyz, the group.

Their second album, The Wait is Over, came out in July 1998 (which was written and recorded in 1997) and featured the single "Woof Woof", which was written for the feature film Dr. Dolittle, starring Eddie Murphy.
